theorem Topology.dense_iff_interior_closure_eq_univ {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X]
    {A : Set X} :
    closure A = (Set.univ : Set X) ↔ interior (closure A) = (Set.univ : Set X) := by
  constructor
  · intro h_dense
    simpa [h_dense] using
      (Topology.interior_closure_eq_univ_of_dense (X := X) (A := A) h_dense)
  · intro h_int
    have h_subset : (Set.univ : Set X) ⊆ closure A := by
      have : interior (closure A) ⊆ closure A := interior_subset
      simpa [h_int] using this
    exact Set.Subset.antisymm (Set.Subset_univ _) h_subset

theorem Topology.closure_eq_univ_of_closure_interior_eq_univ
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X}
    (h : closure (interior A) = (Set.univ : Set X)) :
    closure A = (Set.univ : Set X) := by
  -- Prove the two inclusions separately.
  apply Set.Subset.antisymm
  · -- `closure A` is clearly contained in `univ`.
    exact Set.Subset_univ _
  · -- Since `closure (interior A) ⊆ closure A`, the hypothesis gives the other inclusion.
    have h_subset : closure (interior A) ⊆ closure A :=
      Topology.closure_interior_subset_closure (X := X) (A := A)
    simpa [h] using h_subset

theorem Topology.closure_eq_univ_iff_interior_compl_empty
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    closure A = (Set.univ : Set X) ↔ interior (Aᶜ) = (∅ : Set X) := by
  constructor
  · intro h_closure
    exact
      Topology.interior_compl_eq_empty_of_dense
        (X := X) (A := A) h_closure
  · intro h_int_empty
    classical
    by_contra h_not_dense
    -- Define the open set `U := (closure A)ᶜ`.
    set U : Set X := (closure A)ᶜ with hUdef
    have hU_open : IsOpen U := isClosed_closure.isOpen_compl
    -- Since `A ⊆ closure A`, we have `U ⊆ Aᶜ`.
    have hU_subset : U ⊆ Aᶜ := by
      intro x hxU
      have hx_A : x ∈ A := by
        by_contra h_notA
        exact (hxU ((subset_closure : (A : Set X) ⊆ closure A) (by
          by_cases h : x ∈ A
          · exact h
          · exact (False.elim (h_notA h))))) 
      exact (hxU (subset_closure hx_A)).elim
    -- Because `U` is open and contained in `Aᶜ`, it is contained in `interior (Aᶜ)`.
    have hU_in_int : U ⊆ interior (Aᶜ) :=
      interior_maximal hU_subset hU_open
    -- The complement `U` is nonempty, since `closure A ≠ univ`.
    have hU_nonempty : U.Nonempty := by
      have : (closure A)ᶜ.Nonempty := by
        have hc : closure A ≠ (Set.univ : Set X) := h_not_dense
        by_contra h_empty
        have h_eq : (closure A)ᶜ = (∅ : Set X) :=
          Set.not_nonempty_iff_eq_empty.1 h_empty
        have h_closure_univ : closure A = (Set.univ : Set X) := by
          simpa [hUdef, h_eq] using congrArg (fun s : Set X => sᶜ) h_eq
        exact hc h_closure_univ
      simpa [hUdef] using this
    -- Therefore `interior (Aᶜ)` is nonempty, contradicting the hypothesis.
    rcases hU_nonempty with ⟨x, hxU⟩
    have hx_int : x ∈ interior (Aᶜ) := hU_in_int hxU
    have : x ∈ (∅ : Set X) := by
      simpa [h_int_empty] using hx_int
    exact this.elim

theorem Topology.isClosed_closure_interior_closure
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    IsClosed (closure (interior (closure A))) := by
  -- `closure (interior (closure A))` is a closure, hence closed.
  exact isClosed_closure
